==English==

===Etymology===

Latin ''sibilatio'', from ''[[sibilare]]'', to hiss

===Noun===

{{en-noun}}


# A hissing sound.
*: ''From the shadows emanated a hushed sibilation. "Snakes, they're everywhere!" she exclaimed before running out.''


